{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# CHANGELOG.md: git-cliff, prepend-scoped generate-then-curate from conventional commits\n\n## Why\n\nNo user-facing changelog exists: `docs/release-notes.md` is the agent-facing contract-change log, and GitHub Releases notes are auto-generated. Across nine surveyed Python tools, towncrier (pip/pytest) solves a many-contributor merge-conflict problem rebar doesn't have; ruff/uv generate from PR labels (needs a PR workflow rebar doesn't have); git-cliff converts the conventional-commit discipline rebar already pays for into a changelog. Keep-a-Changelog is the convergent shape (rich's CHANGELOG.md is the exemplar). Rejected alternatives — towncrier (double-entry ceremony), PR-label generation (no PRs), GitHub-Releases-only (no in-repo artifact) — recorded in cliff.toml header comments.\n\n## What\n\n- Add `cliff.toml`. Keys live under their proper sections (a top-level key is silently ignored — e.g. `filter_unconventional` belongs under `[git]`): `[git] conventional_commits = true`, `filter_unconventional = false`, plus a catch-all commit parser so mixed-history commits are kept. `commit_parsers` mapping (this list is normative): `feat:` → Added; `fix:` → Fixed; `!`/BREAKING CHANGE → Breaking (own group, listed first); `perf:`/`refactor:` → Changed; `docs:` → Documentation; drop `build:`/`ci:`/`chore:`/`test:`.\n- **Pin the tool and give it an install path:** pin a git-cliff version (2.x; exact pin chosen at execution against the current release) in a `make changelog` target (checks `git-cliff --version` matches the pin; installation documented as `pipx install git-cliff==<pin>` or `cargo install`, noted in docs/releasing.md so a new maintainer never hits bare \"command not found\"). git-cliff is a standalone Rust binary — it is NOT added to pyproject dev extras.\n- **Curation-safe regeneration (the core mechanism — full-file regen is forbidden after initial generation):** initial generation runs once back through v0.1.0 (ledger quality accepted for history); thereafter the ONLY sanctioned invocation is release-time `git cliff --unreleased --tag vX.Y.Z --prepend CHANGELOG.md`, which prepends the new section and never touches committed (possibly hand-curated) sections. The maintainer then hand-curates the newly prepended section before tagging. `make changelog` encodes exactly this invocation so the destructive full-regen form is never typed by hand.\n- Include `## [Unreleased]` and the compare-link block (rich pattern).\n- `docs/releasing.md` gains the step: `make changelog` → curate the top section (~5 min) → commit → tag. Dial position recorded there: generate-then-edit (pure-generated rejected as ledger-like; mypy-style prose rejected as unsustainable solo).\n- **Repoint `[project.urls]` Changelog** (required edit, currently `docs/release-notes.md` at pyproject.toml:78) → `https://github.com/navapbc/rebar/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md`.\n- Add a one-line pointer at the top of `docs/release-notes.md`: \"User-facing changelog: CHANGELOG.md; this file tracks agent-visible contract changes\" (the epic's cross-link AC, owned here).\n- Known consumer, acknowledged: `src/rebar/llm/code_review/workflow_ops.py:310` classifies CHANGELOG-touching diffs as a hard-to-reverse surface, so curation commits score higher review impact — accepted (changelog edits SHOULD get careful review; no code change).\n\n## Scope\n\nIN: `cliff.toml`, `CHANGELOG.md`, `make changelog` target, `docs/releasing.md` step, pyproject urls repoint, release-notes pointer line.\nOUT: towncrier/news fragments; changing commit conventions; back-editing published GitHub Releases; the auto-generated GitHub Releases notes (complementary channel, unchanged); any change to workflow_ops.py.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `CHANGELOG.md` exists with Keep-a-Changelog headings, `## [Unreleased]`, compare links, entries back to v0.1.0 — prove: `grep -c \"^## \\[\" CHANGELOG.md` ≥ 8 (one per released minor) and `grep -q \"\\[Unreleased\\]\" CHANGELOG.md`.\n- [ ] `cliff.toml`: parsers under `[git]`, the normative mapping above, catch-all present — prove: `grep -A2 \"\\[git\\]\" cliff.toml` shows `filter_unconventional = false`; header comments record the rejected alternatives.\n- [ ] Curation safety — prove: `make changelog` contains `--unreleased` and `--prepend` and no bare full-regen invocation; running `make changelog` twice with no new commits produces no diff (idempotence of the sanctioned path).\n- [ ] `docs/releasing.md` documents install-pin + regenerate-curate-commit-tag ordering — prove: grep for \"git-cliff\" and the version pin.\n- [ ] pyproject Changelog URL points at CHANGELOG.md — prove: `grep \"Changelog\" pyproject.toml` shows the new target. `docs/release-notes.md` carries the pointer line — prove: `head -5 docs/release-notes.md | grep -q CHANGELOG.md`."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783631034944096001,"uuid":"de42da14-32e7-4bc4-b16e-8653bf7c584a"}